track_notes: Route from CP, ascending edge of forest to Pen y Gadair Fawr and then across plateau to summit. Steep in places may require mild scrambling.
Start at CP but take road to Grwyne Fawr Reservoir. Cross dam and head for summit. No discernible path on the ground so careful navigation required in poor visibility
This is a circular route my walking partner devised to link three SOTA summits, to give a full day out in the hills.  This isnt the quickest way to the top.
track_title: A long walk linking three hills.

track_notes: Total time (including ops): 2hr 10m. Maximum difficulty: Swiss Alpine Club Grade T2. Uncurated GPX which may contain navigation errors, detours and hazards. track_notes: Enough room for a couple of cars to park to the side of bridal way at the start. Nice moderate climb to the summit with fantastic views on the way. Clear path to the top. I’d class this as a moderate route.
track_title: Waun Fach GW/SW-002  nice gradual climb to summit
